#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "22. Ūnapañcabandhanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "22. The training rule on less than five mends"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.245"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-np.22.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.22.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.118"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2273"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country at Kapilavatthu in "
"the Banyan Tree Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarena kumbhakārena bhikkhū pavāritā honti—"
msgstr "At that time a potter had invited the monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "“yesaṃ ayyānaṃ pattena attho ahaṃ pattenā”ti."
msgstr "“If any one of you needs a bowl, I’ll provide it.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū patte viññāpenti."
msgstr ""
"But the monks lacked a sense of moderation, and they asked for many bowls."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "Yesaṃ khuddakā pattā te mahante patte viññāpenti."
msgstr "Those who had small bowls asked for large ones,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "Yesaṃ mahantā pattā te khuddake patte viññāpenti."
msgstr "and those who had large bowls asked for small ones."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so kumbhakāro bhikkhūnaṃ bahū patte karonto na sakkoti aññaṃ "
"vikkāyikaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ kātuṃ,"
msgstr ""
"The potter was so busy making bowls for the monks that he was unable to make "
"other goods for sale."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid "attanāpi na yāpeti, puttadārāpissa kilamanti."
msgstr ""
"He could not make a living for himself, and his wife and children suffered."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū patte "
"viññāpessanti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the Sakyan ascetics not have any sense of moderation and ask for "
"many bowls?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ imesaṃ bahū patte karonto na sakkoti aññaṃ vikkāyikaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ kātuṃ,"
msgstr ""
"This potter is so busy making bowls for them that he is unable to make other "
"goods for sale."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "attanāpi na yāpeti, puttadārāpissa kilamantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"He is unable to make a living for himself, and his wife and children are "
"suffering.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2274"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū patte viññāpessantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can those monks not have a sense of moderation and ask for many bowls?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2275"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ "
"ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.18"
msgid ""
"saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū patte viññāpentīti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks are acting like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.19"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.20"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.21"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū patte "
"viññāpessanti."
msgstr ""
"How can those foolish men not have a sense of moderation and ask for many "
"bowls?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.22"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.119"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.23"
msgid "vigarahitvā dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "After criticizing them, he gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.24"
msgid "“na, bhikkhave, patto viññāpetabbo."
msgstr "“Monks, a monk should not ask for a bowl."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.1.25"
msgid "Yo viññāpeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "If he does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.22.1.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2276"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno patto bhinno hoti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards the bowl of a certain monk broke."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so bhikkhu—“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ pattaṃ viññāpetun”ti "
"kukkuccāyanto na viññāpeti."
msgstr ""
"Knowing that the Buddha had prohibited asking for a bowl and being afraid of "
"wrongdoing, he did not ask for a new one."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "Hatthesu piṇḍāya carati."
msgstr "As a consequence he collected almsfood with his hands."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā hatthesu piṇḍāya carissanti, seyyathāpi "
"titthiyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the Sakyan ascetics collect almsfood with their hands, just like "
"ascetics of other sects?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2277"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid ""
"“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, naṭṭhapattassa vā bhinnapattassa vā pattaṃ "
"viññāpetun”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to ask for a new bowl if your bowl has been lost or is "
"broken.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.22.1.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2278"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.120"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ "
"naṭṭhapattassa vā bhinnapattassa vā pattaṃ viññāpetun”ti appamattakenapi "
"bhinnena appamattakenapi khaṇḍena vilikhitamattenapi bahū patte viññāpenti."
msgstr ""
"When they knew about the Master’s allowance, the monks from the group of six "
"asked for many bowls even when their existing bowls only had a minor chip or "
"scratch."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so kumbhakāro bhikkhūnaṃ tatheva bahū patte karonto na sakkoti "
"aññaṃ vikkāyikaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ kātuṃ,"
msgstr ""
"Then that potter was once again so busy making bowls for the monks that he "
"was unable to make other goods for sale."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.3"
msgid "attanāpi na yāpeti, puttadārāpissa kilamanti."
msgstr ""
"He could not make a living for himself, and his wife and children suffered."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.4"
msgid "Manussā tatheva ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "And people grumbled and complained as before."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.5"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū patte "
"viññāpessanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.6"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ imesaṃ bahū patte karonto na sakkoti aññaṃ vikkāyikaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ kātuṃ, "
"attanāpi na yāpeti, puttadārāpissa kilamantī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.246"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2279"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.7"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.8"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.9"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.10"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū appamattakenapi bhinnena appamattakenapi "
"khaṇḍena vilikhitamattenapi bahū patte viññāpessantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six ask for many bowls even if their "
"existing bowls only have a minor chip or scratch?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2280"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.12"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, appamattakenapi bhinnena appamattakenapi "
"khaṇḍena vilikhitamattenapi bahū patte viññāpethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you are acting like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.13"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.14"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.15"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, appamattakenapi bhinnena appamattakenapi "
"khaṇḍena vilikhitamattenapi bahū patte viññāpessatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you ask for many bowls even if your existing bowls only "
"have a minor chip or scratch?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.16"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.17"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.17a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2281"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.18"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu ūnapañcabandhanena pattena aññaṃ navaṃ pattaṃ cetāpeyya, "
"nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk gets a new bowl in exchange for a bowl with less than five mends, "
"he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. VAR: so → so ca (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.19"
msgid "Tena bhikkhunā so patto bhikkhuparisāya nissajjitabbo."
msgstr "That monk should relinquish that bowl to an assembly of monks."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.121"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.20"
msgid ""
"Yo ca tassā bhikkhuparisāya pattapariyanto so tassa bhikkhuno padātabbo—"
msgstr "He should then be given the last bowl belonging to that assembly:"

#. VAR: ayaṃ te → ayante (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.21"
msgid "‘ayaṃ te, bhikkhu, patto yāva bhedanāya dhāretabbo’ti."
msgstr "‘Monk, this bowl is yours; keep it until it breaks.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.22"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcī”ti."
msgstr "This is the proper procedure.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs1.3.23"
msgid "(<em>22</em>:<strong>41</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-np.22.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.22.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2282"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2283"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Ūnapañcabandhano nāma"
msgstr "A bowl with less than five mends:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid ""
"patto abandhano vā ekabandhano vā dvibandhano vā tibandhano vā catubandhano "
"vā."
msgstr "it has no mends, one mend, two mends, three mends, or four mends."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Abandhanokāso nāma patto"
msgstr "A bowl with a mend that does not count:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. That is, a fracture of two finger-breaths, <i lang="pli">dvaṅgulā</i>. For the conversion into metric units I follow the suggestions of BMC I, pp. 565-566.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "yassa dvaṅgulā rāji na hoti."
msgstr "one that does not have a 4 cm long fracture."

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Bandhanokāso nāma patto "
msgstr "A bowl with a mend that counts:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "yassa dvaṅgulā rāji hoti."
msgstr "one that has a 4 cm long fracture."

#. </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Navo nāma"
msgstr "New bowl:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "patto viññattiṃ upādāya vuccati."
msgstr "newly asked for is what is meant."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.247"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2284"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Cetāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets […] in exchange:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "for the act of asking, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyo hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the bowl, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "Saṃghamajjhe nissajjitabbo."
msgstr "It should be relinquished in the midst of the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "Sabbeheva adhiṭṭhitapattaṃ gahetvā sannipatitabbaṃ."
msgstr "All determined bowls should be brought together."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "Na lāmako patto adhiṭṭhātabbo—"
msgstr "You should not determine an inferior bowl, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "“mahagghaṃ pattaṃ gahessāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I’ll get a valuable bowl.”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.122"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "Sace lāmakaṃ pattaṃ adhiṭṭheti—"
msgstr "If you determine an inferior bowl, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "“mahagghaṃ pattaṃ gahessāmī”ti,"
msgstr "“I’ll get a valuable bowl”,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "you commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </span></p><p><span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.24"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbo."
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.25"
msgid ""
"Tena bhikkhunā saṃghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa "
"vacanīyo—"
msgstr ""
"After approaching the Order, that monk should put his upper robe over one "
"shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior monks. He should then "
"squat on his heels, put the palms of his hands together, and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.26"
msgid "“ayaṃ me, bhante, patto ūnapañcabandhanena pattena cetāpito nissaggiyo."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this bowl that I got in exchange for a bowl that had less than "
"five mends is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.27"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.28"
msgid "Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā."
msgstr "” After relinquishing it, he should confess the offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.29"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena āpatti paṭiggahetabbā."
msgstr "The confession should be received by a competent and capable monk."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.30"
msgid "Pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato bhikkhu pattaggāhāpako sammannitabbo—"
msgstr ""
"A monk who has five qualities should be appointed as the bowl-distributor:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.31"
msgid ""
"yo na chandāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na dosāgatiṃ gaccheyya, na mohāgatiṃ gaccheyya, "
"na bhayāgatiṃ gaccheyya, gāhitāgāhitañca jāneyya."
msgstr ""
"one who is not swayed by desire, ill will, confusion, or fear, and who "
"understands the meaning of distributed and not distributed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.32"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo."
msgstr "“And, monks, this is how he should be appointed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.33"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo."
msgstr "First the monk should be asked"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.34"
msgid "Yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Order:"

#. </p><div class="kamma"><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2285"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.35"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "‘Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.36"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ pattaggāhāpakaṃ "
"sammanneyya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, it should appoint monk so-and-so as "
"the bowl-distributor."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.37"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2286"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.38"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.39"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ pattaggāhāpakaṃ sammannati."
msgstr "The Order appoints monk so-and-so as the bowl-distributor."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.40"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno pattaggāhāpakassa sammuti, so "
"tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who agrees to appointing monk so-and-so as the bowl-distributor "
"should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.41"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not agree should say so."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2287"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.123"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.42"
msgid "Sammato saṃghena itthannāmo bhikkhu pattaggāhāpako."
msgstr "The Order has appointed monk so-and-so as the bowl-distributor."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.43"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī,"
msgstr "The Order approves and is therefore silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.44"
msgid "evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr "I will remember it thus.’”"

#. </p></div><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2288"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.45"
msgid "Tena sammatena bhikkhunā patto gāhetabbo."
msgstr "The appointed monk should give away that bowl."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.46"
msgid "Thero vattabbo—"
msgstr "He should tell the most senior monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.47"
msgid "“gaṇhātu, bhante, thero pattan”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, would you like this bowl?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.48"
msgid "Sace thero gaṇhāti, therassa patto dutiyassa gāhetabbo."
msgstr ""
"If the most senior monk takes it, his bowl should be offered to the next "
"monk."

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.49"
msgid "Na ca tassa anuddayatāya na gahetabbo."
msgstr "He should not not take that bowl out of sympathy."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.50"
msgid "Yo na gaṇheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.51"
msgid "Apattakassa na gāhetabbo."
msgstr "It is not to be offered to anyone who does not have bowl."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.52"
msgid "Eteneva upāyena yāva saṃghanavakā gāhetabbo."
msgstr ""
"In this manner it should be offered all the way to the most junior monk in "
"the Order."

#. </p><hr><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.53"
msgid ""
"Yo ca tassā bhikkhuparisāya pattapariyanto, so tassa bhikkhuno padātabbo—"
msgstr ""
"He is then to be given the last bowl belonging to that assembly of monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.54"
msgid "“ayaṃ te, bhikkhu, patto yāva bhedanāya dhāretabbo”ti."
msgstr "‘Monk, this bowl is yours; keep it until it breaks’:"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2289"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.124"></a><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.55"
msgid ""
"Tena bhikkhunā so patto na adese nikkhipitabbo, na abhogena bhuñjitabbo, na "
"vissajjetabbo—"
msgstr ""
"That monk is not to store that bowl in an unsuitable place, to use it in an "
"unsuitable way, or to give it away, thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.56"
msgid "“kathāyaṃ patto nasseyya vā vinasseyya vā bhijjeyya vā”ti?"
msgstr "“How may this bowl be lost, destroyed, or broken?”"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.57"
msgid ""
"Sace adese vā nikkhipati abhogena vā bhuñjati vissajjeti vā, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he stores it in an unsuitable place, uses it in an unsuitable way, or "
"gives it away, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. </span></span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2290"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.58"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti"
msgstr "This is the proper procedure:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np22:pts-cs2.1.59"
msgid "ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā."
msgstr "this is in right method."

